('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2875, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Neurobiology is a relative young field of study on the cutting edge of multiple disciplines such as biology, psychology, philosophy and computer science. \n\nConsequently, the brain is approached from a biomedical point of view, from the molecule to the mind. The support of several university institutes such as the Swammerdam Institute of Life Sciences (SILS-CNS) and other neurobiological institutes like the Netherlands Institute for Neuroscience (NIN) and the AMC guarantee excellent courses and internships.', 'Biomedical Sciences: Neurobiology', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2876, 'academic master', 'research', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'As well as the fundamental neuroscience disciplines, brain imaging, systems neurophysiology and computation are strongly featured here. \n\nA typical question for this track would be: How do neural processes such as spikes and synaptic plasticity give rise to memory, conscious perception and behavioural decisions?\n\nThis track aims to understand how the brain implements cognitive processes not only by studying information processing in the healthy, active brain, but also by using computer stimulation and interventional approaches that target causal functions. The pathological brain and the healthy brain are of equal interest in this track, and are studied on the basis of neurological and psychiatric disorders.', 'Brain and Cognitive Science (research MSc)', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2877, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'This programme gives you the tools and knowledge you need to work for a wide range of organisations in both the commercial and governmental sectors. It is a specialised\nprogramme for students with a background in business economics who want to focus on organisational and financing issues.', 'Business Economics: Finance', '156'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2878, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The Organisation Economics track of the MSc in Business Economics examines the economic performance of organisations in broad terms by looking at staff motivation, allocation of decision making powers, investment decisions, corporate governance and corporate functioning in various types of markets.', 'Business Economics: Organisation Economics', '156'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2879, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Real estate is a specialist discipline, covering the development, financing and operation of real estate. This specialisation links academic scholarship to industrial practice, thanks to the University''s collaboration with industry.', 'Business Economics: Real Estate Finance', '156'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2880, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The curriculum combines one year of Earth Science courses and one specialised year concentrating on management aspects in Earth Science, interdisciplinary skills and an internship in a company or (non) governmental organisation. Graduates of this track are well equipped to develop a successful career as an applied earth scientist. Such specialists are highly demanded to tackle the challenges of climate change and to translate scientific process knowledge into management strategies in order to lessen the effects for society.\n\nWhat you can expect from Environmental Management at the University of Amsterdam:\n\n?an inspiring scientific environment where scientist work in a stimulating interdisciplinary setting on the cutting edge between physical geography, ecology, hydrology and environmental chemistry, combined in the Institute for Biodiversity and Ecosystem Dynamics (IBED)\n?IBED offers you a wide range of brand new and state of the art facilities (E-science labs including GIS, Remote sensing and geo-ecological modelling, Soil- and environmental chemistry as well erosion labs) to enable you to let your work meet the latest scientific standards.', 'Earth Sciences: Environmental Management', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2881, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Students deal with complex relationships between biogeochemical and geomorphological processes in terrestrial and adjacent aquatic ecosystems, and the influences of climate change and direct human impact. These relationships will be studied at different scales: from a molecular to a global level. Students focus on measurement techniques, combining laboratory experiments with field inventories and monitoring programmes. They can also focus on computer modelling with GIS, remote sensing, spatial statistics or computer simulation models.\n\n', 'Earth Sciences: Geo-ecological Dynamics', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2882, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, '', 'Econometrics: Financial Econometrics', '156'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2883, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, '', 'Econometrics: Mathematical Economics', '156'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2884, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The Advanced Matter and Energy Physics programme is for students interested in:\n\n?next generation energy materials and processes\n?unconventional superconductivity\n?strongly correlated electron systems \n?quantum gases \n?quantum information & quantum simulation with ultracold atoms\n?soft condensed and biomatter\n?complex liquids\n\nThis track offers the chance to take part in research into ''hot'' topics such as:\n\n?next generation energy materials, such as nanocrystals, nanowires and nanophotonic systems for tomorrow''s solar energy conversion\n?emergence: the surprising and theoretically mysterious properties condensed matter systems exhibit when they are sufficiently complex\n?properties of complex liquids, granular, soft and biomatter including jamming and self-organisation\n?properties of new forms of ultracold atomic quantum matter, including strong correlations and entanglement \n?unravelling how new (un)conventional superconductors work and how they can be applied as q-bits, field sensors, magnets or in power applications', 'Physics: Advanced Matter and Energy Physics', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2885, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The programme is looking for students who are interested in:\n\n?the smallest particles in the Universe, \n?the way these particles interact, \n?matter and anti-matter, \n?the Higgs particle, \n?neutrinos from supernovae or from our Sun, \n?the search for dark matter and, \n?the detection of gravitational waves.\n\nThis Master''s track offers the chance to reflect on current research topics such as:\n\n?the search for the Higgs particles;\n?physics beyond the Standard Model;\n?the first detection of cosmic neutrinos; gravitational waves or dark matter particles.', 'Physics: Particle and Astroparticle Physics', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2886, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The programme is for students interested in one or more of the following subjects:\n\n?the study of physical processes in the human body, organs, cells and macromolecules;\n?the use of advanced biophysical methods to study macromolecules at the single-molecule level and to study biological processes down to femtosecond timescales;\n?the development and improvement of technology for medical diagnostics and therapy;\n?the interaction of light and/or radiation with cells and tissues (biomedical photonics);\n?the manipulation of tissues and cells by light or radiation to improve diagnosis and monitoring.\n\nThis Master''s track offers the chance to reflect on research topics such as: \n?the quest for quantitative functional monitoring and imaging of living tissue;\n?working in multidisciplinary research teams with physicists, chemists, biologists, engineers and medical professionals; \n?theoretical knowledge and hands-on experience in biomedical imaging, molecular and cellular biophysics and photonics;\n?research and development of new methods for diagnosis and monitoring.', 'Physics: Physics of Life and Health', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2887, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The programme is looking for students who:\n\n* are interested in unravelling the laws of science and understanding how they work; \n* want to analyse why matter is what it is and how that affects the world around us; \n* you intend to contribute to other disciplines of science by grasping the concept of matter at the fundamental level; \n* are fascinated by physics; \n* have a high ability for abstraction; \n* enjoy elaborating mathematical models; \n* are willing to dig deep to find solutions for theoretical physics problems.\n\nIn this Master''s track you will reflect on current research topics such as quantum systems, quantum information and soft matter as in the physics of living matter. Further more you will focus on particle physics; string theory, cosmology and the standard model.', 'Physics: Theoretical Physics', '155'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2888, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The Conflict Resolution and Governance programme provides students with a theoretical basis for analysing conflicts and the relationship of these conflicts to concerns for democratic governance. The case-oriented approach helps students to develop skills and experience through the analysis of action in settings that are grounded in comparative and historical perspectives. Students gain the ability to apply different theoretical orientations to make sense of the range of global, regional and local influences that shape conflicts and their relationship to governance. The programme''s ambition is to develop students'' capacity to draw on the most vexing features of contemporary conflicts to form governance regimes from the fabric of local crisis.', 'Conflict Resolution and Governance', '158'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2889, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Which challenges do cities and urban regions face in an era of globalisation and who are the winners and the losers?What is the role of boundaries in shaping and solving conflicts? How can we manage our use of natural resources in such a way as to minimalise the environmental degradation on all geographical scales?\n\nQuestions like these touch upon the relationship between humans, societies and space, a relationship typical for the field of study of Human Geography. It analyses the way humans use and understand the world, the spatial differentiation and organisation of human activity and its interrelationships with the physical environment. \n\nThis programme is intended for students who wish to explore social phenomena on various scales – global, national, or local – from a socio-spatial perspective. The programme includes relevant academic research methods and techniques, and it offers students the opportunity to advance the knowledge of geographical information systems.', 'Sociale geografie', '158'),
('', 'UNK', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2890, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The Forensics track aims to make you a specialist in forensic intelligence. As a forensic analyst, you are responsible for tracing digital evidence on all levels, from a single computer to a large network. What activities were performed? Which errors were intentionally made and where were they hidden? Are certain files missing and where can they be found? To answer these kind of questions, you need the profound knowledge this Master has to offer. Not only will you be able to track down cybercrime, you will also learn how to document your evidence in a way that others can understand and will even hold up in court.', 'System and Network Engineering: Networking', '155'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2891, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, 'What a culture identifies as a dialogue with another culture is a sometimes fruitful and sometimes conflictual but always productive moment that reveals that no “culture” is a self-contained historical or geographical entity. Using interdisciplinary concepts and objects, the course proposes to explore the dialogues between and therefore (self-)redefinition of cultural phenomena, with a special emphasis on issues of mobility and identity construction.\n\n', 'Arts and Culture: Comparative Cultural Analysis', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 120, 24, 'full-time', 2892, 'academic master', 'research', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Wil je je kennis van de archeologie verder uitdiepen en bijvoorbeeld meer te weten komen over de betekenis van tempels in de antieke wereld? Of wil je de ontwikkeling van steden in Noordwest-Europa vanaf de laat-Romeinse tijd ''diepgravend'' bestuderen? Binnen de tweejarige onderzoeksmaster Archeologie krijg je hiertoe ruimschoots de gelegenheid. Je kunt kiezen tussen de specialisaties Europese archeologie en Mediterrane archeologie. \n\n', 'Archeologie (research MA)', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'part-time', 2893, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'en', 1, '', 0, 0, '', 'Arts and Culture: Comparative Cultural Analysis', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 90, 18, 'full-time', 2894, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Musea zijn de spiegels van de tijd. De wijze waarop collecties worden gerangschikt, heeft te maken met het verhaal dat het museum wil vertellen. Wélke verhalen verteld moeten worden, is een vraag die aan een voortdurend proces van verandering onderhevig is. Als je voor een museum wilt werken, is het voor Nederland unieke duale programma Museumstudies een goede keuze. De studie bereidt je voor op wetenschappelijke functies in musea, zoals educatieve functies, banen als pr- of beleidsmedewerker of organisator van tentoonstellingen.\n\nDe zorg voor de kwaliteit van de ontvangst van publiek is net zo belangrijk geworden als de zorg voor de collectie. Internationalisering en globalisering vereisen voortdurende positiebepaling: in gevarieerde onderwerpen van tentoonstellingen, in het verzamelbeleid, in museale netwerken, in internationaal bruikleenverkeer en in het onderwijs van de jeugd. \n\nMuseumstudies is een duaal programma: een academische voorbereiding op een specifiek beroep. Een praktijkperiode vormt een belangrijk onderdeel van de studie. Amsterdam is dé museumstad bij uitstek: je vindt hier het grootste aantal musea en monumenten in Nederland.', 'Erfgoedstudies: Museumstudies', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2895, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Het programma Europees beleid is een interdisciplinair studieprogramma, dat de Europese bestuurspraktijk vanuit verschillende invalshoeken belicht. Het vakkenpakket gaat in op politieke, economische, juridische, culturele en historische aspecten van Europees beleid. Het Europese openbaar bestuur wordt hierin zeer ruim opgevat als alle activiteiten met betrekking tot het vormgeven van de Europese bestuurs- en beleidspraktijk op lokaal, regionaal, landelijk en Europees niveau. Aspecten van het Europees beleid worden bestudeerd vanuit de overheid, het bedrijfsleven, het maatschappelijk middenveld (ngo''s) en de individuele burger.\n\nAls je een loopbaan bij de Nederlandse of Europese overheid ambieert, dan is het masterprogramma Europees beleid een uitstekende voorbereiding.\n\n', 'Europese studies: Europees beleid', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2896, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Het eenjarige masterprogramma Oost-Europese studies aan de UvA verschaft je kennis en inzicht in de geschiedenis van en de recente ontwikkelingen in de Oost-Europese landen. Dit gebeurt nadrukkelijk in een internationale context. Het programma bestrijkt een breed gebied: van Midden- en Oost-Europa, inclusief Rusland, tot Centraal-Azië en de Kaukasus. \n\nHet vakkenaanbod is thematisch en loopt uiteen van bijvoorbeeld ''Communisme in Oost-Europa'', ''Nieuwe media in Rusland'' en ''Publieke sfeer'' tot ''Islam en politiek in Rusland''. Centraal staat het verplichte vakcluster over ''Mass Politics'' en de ''Post-Soviet States''. \n\nDe masterscriptie waarmee je het programma afsluit omvat 18 studiepunten en is een individueel onderzoeksproject begeleid door twee docenten. Het onderwerp van je onderzoek moet aansluiten bij het programma van Oost-Europese studies en wordt gekozen in het kader van je verplichte vakcluster.\n\n', 'Europese studies: Oost Europese studies', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2897, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Het programma Geschiedenis van de Internationale Betrekkingen hanteert een definitie van het vakgebied die meer omvat dan alleen de staat en de betrekkingen tussen staten. Het uitgangspunt van het programma is de beslissende betekenis van de unieke historische context bij de bestudering van onderdelen van de internationale betrekkingen. Hiermee onderscheidt het programma Geschiedenis van de Internationale Betrekkingen zich duidelijk van de leer der internationale betrekkingen die afkomstig is uit de sociale wetenschappen. In de sociale wetenschappen gaat de leer uit van theorievorming, bijvoorbeeld de ''realistische'' theorie dat staten met elkaar in conflict komen doordat ze onvermijdelijk hun nationale belangen najagen. (Historische gebeurtenissen ondersteunen in dat geval een theorie, maar kunnen ook gebruikt worden om een theorie te weerleggen.) In het masterprogramma Geschiedenis van de Internationale Betrekkingen is er zeker ook aandacht voor algemene modellen en theorieën, maar uitsluitend als hulpmiddel om historische gebeurtenissen eventueel in hun unieke karakter te kunnen verklaren. De analyse van de specifiek-historische situatie is het uitgangspunt. \n\n', 'Geschiedenis: Geschiedenis van de internationale betrekkingen', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'part-time', 2898, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, '', 'Geschiedenis: Geschiedenis van de internationale betrekkingen', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2899, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Goed vertalen vereist een groot aantal vaardigheden. In de eerste plaats uiteraard het adequaat omzetten van geschreven tekst uit de brontaal naar de doeltaal, in ons geval het Nederlands. Hierbij moet de vertaler permanent oog blijven houden voor zowel de context waarin de brontekst geschreven werd, als de context van de doeltaal, waarin de lezer van de vertaling zich bevindt. Maar er komt meer bij kijken: revisie en redactie van vertalingen, de correctie ervan, de interpretatieverschillen die kunnen ontstaan... en soms moet er ook getolkt worden.\n\nIn het programma Vertalen ontwikkel je enerzijds de vaardigheid om het vertalen als proces en de vertaling als eindproduct te beoordelen. Dit is de theoretische kant van de opleiding. De praktische kant is je specialisatie in de taal van je keuze, de brontaal van waaruit je gaat vertalen naar je doeltaal (en andersom). Daarnaast heb je de mogelijkheid stage te lopen bij een vertaalbureau, een internationale instelling of een andere werkgever die met vertalers werkt. Omdat vertalers te maken krijgen met digitale techniek zijn ook enkele ICT-disciplines in de profileringsruimte van het curriculum opgenomen.\n\n\n', 'Taalwetenschappen: Vertalen', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2900, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'The linguistic landscape of Europe is a fascinating one. On the one hand there is enormous diversity: with languages as diverse as Russian, Spanish and Swedish, the linguistic differences seem to be immense. On the other hand, the long history of expansion and subsequent withdrawal of populations like the Romans, the Celts, the Ottomans, and the Slavs have led to a mixture of recurrent linguistic properties across Europe or parts of Europe. Furthermore, due to its long colonial history many European languages are now world languages too, which adds a global dimension to the study of European languages and the way they interact with other languages.  \n\nThe language (groups) that you can choose from Dutch, English, French, German, Italian, Scandinavian, Slavonic, Spanish. You then add to this a second component, which can be either thematic or concern a second language. Thematic expansions are for instance Second Language Acquisition, Sociolinguistics, Phonetics, or Theoretical Linguistics. ', 'Linguistics: Linguistics of European Languages', '157'),
('', 'MSc', 'government', 0, 60, 12, 'full-time', 2901, 'academic master', 'regular', 2012, 0, 'nl', 1, '', 0, 0, 'Bij Europese studies aan de UvA verdiep je je bijvoorbeeld in Europees recht, het ontstaan van Europa, de Europese eenwording en de cultuurgeschiedenis van Europa. Streefde Julius Caesar al naar een verenigd Europa toen hij bijna de gehele bekende wereld uit zijn tijd in één rijk samenbracht? Zo nee, wanneer is het concept Europa dan ontstaan? Worden we binnenkort een Europa met federale staten, zoals de Verenigde Staten? En wat zijn de gevolgen van de komst van de euro voor de nationale economieën? Al deze vragen kun je straks door je studie benaderen vanuit een samenhangende interdisciplinaire kennis over Europa. \n\nJe kiest uit een van de volgende studiepaden:\n- Geschiedenis van de Europese eenheid;\n- Cultuur en identiteit in Europa;\n- Institutionele integratie van Europa.\n\n', 'Europese studies', '157'),
